<p>The whole experience was actually a lot easier than I thought after the initial shock to my system and I got a lot of out it. I felt healthier, better in myself, more disciplined and - strangely - more productive.</p>
<p>As well as this I started to get an entirely new outlook on food, drink, wastage and appreciation of the little things. Waiting all day for water and for food really made me appreciate how lucky I am to be able to have it whenever I want, and often over-indulge as well - which I’ll be doing less of now.</p>

